MCQ: What type of learning algorithm builds a mathematical model of a set of data that contains both the inputs and the desired outputs?
Choices: a: Unsupervised learning | b: Reinforcement learning | c: Supervised learning | d: Semi-supervised learning

MCQ: Which type of algorithm is used when the outputs are restricted to a limited set of values?
Choices: a: Regression algorithm | b: Clustering algorithm | c: Classification algorithm | d: Dimensionality reduction algorithm

MCQ: What is the main goal of reinforcement learning?
Choices: a: To find structures in unlabeled data | b: To build a mathematical model of data | c: To take actions in an environment to maximize cumulative reward | d: To reduce the number of random variables under consideration

MCQ: Which type of learning algorithm falls between unsupervised learning and supervised learning?
Choices: a: Reinforcement learning | b: Semi-supervised learning | c: Dimensionality reduction | d: Self-learning

MCQ: What is the process of reducing the number of random variables under consideration by obtaining a set of principal variables?
Choices: a: Feature extraction | b: Cluster analysis | c: Dimensionality reduction | d: Active learning
